Description: Round-topped limestone stela; at the top are nine columns of Hieroglyphic text flanked by two painted wedjat-eyes; below are eighteen rows of Hieroglyphic text; lower left corner is object EA26804.
Curator's comments: Attached to 1891,0716.3 J. Quaegebeur, Chronique d'Egypte 49 (1974), 67-8 (no. 18).
